glance, hid h$$ face, fai$$ly articulating, &startq;O, don't let
it &s;ee us! don't let it &s;ee us! I am &s;$re it's nothing na|tural!
I dare &s;ay it's &s;omebody walking!</P>
<P>The next in&s;tant&punc; they perceived a man, looking ear|ne&s;tly
around&punc; as if to di&s;cover who had echoed the
&s;cream; the place they occupied was in the &s;hade, and
he did not ob&s;erve them. He &s;oon ru&s;hed ha&s;tily on,
and &s;eized the white garment of the flying figure, which
