&s;hall I not owe to you?&endq;</P>
<P>The moon now &s;hining full upon her face, Camilla
&s;aw &s;eated on it youth, &s;en&s;ibility, and beauty. Her
plea&s;ure, involuntarily rather than rationally, was re|doubled
that &s;he had proved &s;erviceable to her as&punc; in
equal proportion&punc; was her abhorrence of the man who
had cau&s;ed the di&s;turbance.</P>
<P>The three females were now proceeding, when the
