little reflexion to benefit by ob&s;erving the mi&s;ery of an
alliance not mentally a&s;&s;orted; and grew up with no
other de&s;ire but to enter the &s;tate her&s;elf, from an ardent
impatience to &s;hake off the &s;lavery &s;he experienced in
&s;inglene&s;s. The recent death of her mother had given
her, indeed, &s;omewhat more liberty; but &s;he had not
&s;ufficient &s;en&s;e to endure any re&s;traint, and langui&s;hed
