<P>This reply was a &s;en&s;ible gratification to Lady Ali|thea,
who, having heard her warmly admired by Lord
O'Lerney, had been the more &s;u&s;ceptible to her ridi|cule.
Rudene&s;s &s;he could have de&s;pi&s;ed without emo|tion;
but contempt had &s;omething in it of in&s;olence; a
