<P>Mr. Dennel &s;oftened a little here into &s;omething like
a &s;mile; and drew two guineas from his pur&s;e; but
more there was no obtaining.</P>
<P>&startq;Come,&endq; cried Sir Sedley, &startq;you have canva&s;&s;ed
well &s;o far. Now for your fair &s;elf.&endq;</P>
<P>&startq;You are a &s;hocking creature!&endq; cried &s;he; don't
you know I am turned mi&s;er?&endq;</P>
<P>Yet &s;he gave her guinea.</P>
<P>&startq;But the fair Tyrolda does not al&s;o, I tru&s;t, a&s;&s;ume
that character?&endq;</P>
<P>Camilla had felt very unea&s;y during this conte&s;t; and
now, colouring, &s;aid &s;he did not mean to go to the
ball.</P>
<P>&startq;Can you ev$r expect, then,&endq; &s;aid Mrs. Arlbery,
&startq;to have a partner at any other? You don't know the
rules of the&s;e places. The ma&s;ter of the ceremonies
